{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"agent_message","text":"The resolver bug is clearer now: `listCoordinates` and `tckClean` only return coordinates when `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/` exists. `akka-serialization-jackson_3:2.6.21` has tests and an `index.json`, but no versioned metadata directory, so the harness drops it even though CI still tries to test it. I’m checking whether that absence is intentional and whether the minimal fix belongs in the resolver or in the generated library files."}}
